begin\": 1885, \"end\": 1906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Worthington\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Worthington\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Worthington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Worthington\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"freestyle silver\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1880}, {\"ngram\": \"no position\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 1925}, {\"ngram\": \"her title\", \"from\": 1936, \"to\": 1945}, {\"ngram\": \"mental struggles\", \"from\": 1952, \"to\": 1968}, {\"ngram\": \"the racing\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 1989}, {\"ngram\": \"Beth Shriever\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2004}, {\"ngram\": \"the heats\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2021}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Pidcock's determination and skill delivered mountain bike gold after Anna Henderson's strong silver in the women's time trial, but too many other winnable medals got away - not least when Josh Tarling punctured during the time trial.\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2302, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2065, \"end\": 2076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Pidcock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Pidcock\"}, {\"begin\": 2138, \"end\": 2152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"score\": 0.9999958972009645, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\"}, {\"begin\": 2257, \"end\": 2261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"score\": 0.980608677117551, \"rank\": 0.019406953848808212, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"skill\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2102}, {\"ngram\": \"mountain bike gold\", \"from\": 2113, \"to\": 2131}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's time trial\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2194}, {\"ngram\": \"too many other winnable medals\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2230}, {\"ngram\": \"the time trial\", \"from\": 2287, \"to\": 2301}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the velodrome, gold for the women's team sprint was a major success after years of hard work to turn around the biggest weakness in the squad.\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2449, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the velodrome\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2320}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2322, \"to\": 2326}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's team sprint\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2354}, {\"ngram\": \"a major success\", \"from\": 2359, \"to\": 2374}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 2381, \"to\": 2386}, {\"ngram\": \"hard work\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2399}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest weakness\", \"from\": 2415, \"to\": 2435}, {\"ngram\": \"the squad\", \"from\": 2439, \"to\": 2448}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it would be the only track gold.\", \"from\": 2450, \"to\": 2486, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the only track gold\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2485}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the face of huge hype, Emma Finucane, 21, added keirin and individual bronze to her haul.\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2580, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2539, \"end\": 2545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9124602677890327e-51, \"text\": \"keirin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the face\", \"from\": 2491, \"to\": 2499}, {\"ngram\": \"huge hype\", \"from\": 2503, \"to\": 2512}, {\"ngram\": \"individual bronze\", \"from\": 2550, \"to\": 2567}, {\"ngram\": \"her haul\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2579}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Familiar faces like Elinor Barker and Jack Carlin fought hard - Barker taking team pursuit bronze and then Madison silver with Neah Evans, while Carlin showed dogged determination to win team sprint silver and individual bronze, picking up scraps behind the dominant Dutch to repeat his haul from Tokyo.\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2602, \"end\": 2615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elinor_Barker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elinor Barker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elinor_Barker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elinor_Barker\"}, {\"begin\": 2620, \"end\": 2624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"score\": 0.9951600819922033, \"rank\": 0.004863431276479572, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Harkness\"}, {\"begin\": 2625, \"end\": 2631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999999684646359, \"rank\": 3.153530928948571e-08, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}, {\"begin\": 2689, \"end\": 2696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 0.9066656517846448, \"rank\": 0.10294241105479368, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}, {\"begin\": 2709, \"end\": 2719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neah_Evans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Neah Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbp